IRS990.ActivityOrMissionDesc: Mission statement 2022: We empower and support families and youth struggling with behavioral emotional or substance abuse challenges in navigating resources to achieve wellness and resilience.

IRS990.Desc: Behavioral Health Peer Support Services to Youth & Families including 1:1 support and Mentoring peer wellness coaching support groups resource and referral services System of Care navigation employment and education support parenting education self-advocacy Life & coping skills and social events that increase self- esteem community connection and natural supports. Services include training and education for Youth & Family Leadership Development and Peer Workforce Development Services: to increase long term recovery and stability for Youth & Family to improve family resiliency and increase community equity. Training and support included: Youth & Family driven Volunteer Services Certified Peer Counseling training Personal Wellness Coaching Youth mentor training Crisis and Cultural awareness Training. Providing job coaching and training support to increase participation in leadership advocacy for System change family and Youth advisory groups and inclusion on internal organizational workgroups.

ProgSrvcAccomActy2Grp.Desc: Youth & Families Focused Technical Assistance and partnerships to increase access to services leverage existing resources reduce gaps in services reduce youth violence reduce stigma and engage with Youth & Family voice with in serving System of Care including community behavioral health agencies schools and education districts criminal justice and domestic violence family support organizations BIPOC community- based organizations and housing and homeless services.

SupplementalInformationDetail.ExplanationTxt: In early 2022 we conducted a general review of Policies and Procedures and update systems and technology to increase capacity. We began the process of organizational assessments to align with Social Determinants of Health National Standards for Youth and Family led Peer and Recovery support organizations as well as required our cultural and community standards. These assessments included reviewing practices from Trauma Informed anti-racist and community equity lens. The immediate shift was more inclusion and empowerment of stakeholders' voices of Youth & Families in all aspects of GPS services and technical assistance on peer support community equity and trauma informed practices within the System of Care partners that serve youth & families.
2nd quarter of 2022 the Bylaws were updated with our interim executive director to reflect recent changes in Washington State Law.

Prior to completing the 990- all officers have been presented with 2022 Year-end financial reports used to complete the 990 form. A committee of BOD members and the executive director completed and reviewed the 990 prior to filing. Once filed it is posted via Basecamp for all officers to review.

Prior to completing the 990- all officers have been presented with 2022 Year-end financial reports used to complete the 990 form. The executive director and members of the BOD completed the 990 form and the following BOD officers: President and Secretary accessed 990 for review prior to filing. Once filed it is posted via Basecamp hub for all members and officers to review.

Conflict of interest statements are signed annually. In the event of a conflict of interest there would be a review conducted by the Board Development Commitee BDC would review the issue including interviewing any necessary persons. The BDC would then present the findings of the review and recommendations to the full BOD. The Full BOD would vote on the final decision.

A BOD conducts annual performance reviews of ED including staff and stakeholder and BOD review committee. The committee reviews all evaluations and researches current wage reports. Recommendations for any changes to ED expectations improvement and or recognition of effort and any resulting compensation changes are presented to the full BOD and a vote is required to implement changes. The BOD themselves undergo self- assessments and review officer roles annually. The ED is responsible for conducting annual performance reviews with key staff. The interim executive director conducted a reviewed job description performance standards and goals with all staff in 2022. Salaries and Organizational roles for all key staff were reviewed by the new executive director in December 2022

Copies of all records open to public disclosure are available to view in our operations office including governing document conflict of interest policies and financial statements. and monthly public by request Records are reviewed monthly by ED and BOD officer bi-monthly at BOD public meetings; and are then hard copies are stored filed quarterly and can be viewed by contacting our operations coordinator or our executive director. Request to view electronic versions of documents can be made via email at info@guidedpathways.org.

We had audit in 2022 for our 2021 tax year by an independent CPA agency. Due to staffing shortages at the CPA attempted to schedule an audit in May but at this time are still waiting for an audit of 2022 financial year.
